(201, 'science', 'oral presentation', 'The Adsorption of Heavy Metals Ions from Green Synthesis Nanoparticles Fe3O4  based on Pleomele Angustifolia from the Batanghari River Iron Sand as Water Purifier', 'Lucky Zaehir Maulana *, Frastica Deswardani, Rista Mutia Anggraini, Febri Berthalita Pujaningsih, and Muhammad Ficky Afrianto, Ade Malemna, and Lamria Br Galingging', 'Department of Physics, Faculty of Science and Technology, Universitas Jambi', 'Since the ancient era, the river is the center of the civilization. Jambi is also famous due to the long line Batanghari river. Most of the economy comes from the exploration of the sediment. Those sediments have an abundance of minerals. Iron oxide is one promising mineral that can be synthesized into nanoparticle magnetic Fe3O4 (Magnetite). On the other side, wet methods, which are common methods, need a lot of chemical solutions. Here, we successfully synthesize magnetic nanoparticles based on green synthesis incorporating Pleomele Angustifolia as the green agent. The end product of this research will utilize the nanoparticles as a water purifier. For that purpose, we characterize our sample with several methods, such as UV-Vis, FTIR, and XRD. The results show that our nanoparticle Fe3O4 is promising as a water purifier adsorbent.', 'Green synthesis, pleomele angustifolia, magnetite, heavy metal.', 'Lucky Zaehir Maulana', 212, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS201-Lucky Zaehir Maulana.pdf', NULL, '2024-10-03 09:07:17', '2024-10-04 14:17:43');
