(202, 'engineering', 'oral presentation', 'Development of Air Manjunto Watershed Flood Inundation Model USING HEC-RAS', 'Gusta Gunawan', 'University of Bengkulu, Civil Engineering Departement, ', 'Abstract. This study presents the development of a flood inundation model using HEC-RAS for the Manjunto Watershed, aiming to enhance predictive accuracy and flood management strategies. Employing a robust mathematical simulation approach, the model integrates peak discharge predictions for a 50-year return period, derived from the synthetic unit hydrograph (SUH) ITB-1 and Nakayasu methods. The HEC-RAS outputs are further refined into detailed flood inundation maps using Arc-GIS 10.8. Comparative analysis of flow rates from the Nakayasu and ITB-1 models against observed data reveals peak flows of approximately 1,400 m³/s, with Nakayasu predicting higher peaks around 1,600 m³/s, and ITB-1 lower peaks around 1,100 m³/s. The spatial analysis of flood depths within the Manjunto Watershed offers critical insights into flood risk distribution, markedly influenced by topographical variations. The resulting flood depth maps delineate high, moderate, and low-risk zones, providing essential data for targeted flood mitigation efforts in Mukomuko Regency, Bengkulu Province. This research underscores the imperative for precise, localized flood management strategies to mitigate future flood risks effectively.', 'Flood, SUH, HEC-RAS, Manjunto Watershed, GIS', 'Gusta Gunawan', 233, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS202-Gusta Gunawan.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS202-Gusta Gunawan.pdf', '2024-10-03 09:08:13', '2024-10-07 06:52:36'),
(203, 'engineering', 'oral presentation', 'test', 'tes', 'unja', 'unja', '123', 'testing1', 237, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS203-testing1.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS203-testing1.pdf', '2024-10-03 14:47:12', '2024-10-03 15:13:08'),
(204, 'science', 'oral presentation', 'Preliminary Study of a Room Light Intensity, Temperature, and Humidity Measurement System Based on DHT11 and BH1750 Sensors', 'Jesi Pebralia*1), Yoza Fendriani 1), Muhammad Ficky Afrianto 1)', 'Physics Department, Jambi University, Indonesia', 'Indoor light intensity, temperature, and humidity are among the physical parameters that can affect indoor air quality as regulated by the Minister of Health Regulation (PERMENKES) of the Republic of Indonesia No. 2 of 2023. In this study, a preliminary investigation of a light intensity measurement system based on the BH1750 sensor and a temperature measurement system based on the DHT11 sensor was conducted. The purpose of this research is to evaluate the performance of the sensor-based measurement system. The research method used is the research and development method with a waterfall model. Data collection was carried out in a meeting room. The results of the study show that the sensor-based measurement system works well, with an accuracy level of 90.13% and an error rate of 9.87%.', 'BH1750 sensor, DHT11 sensor, humidity, indoor light intensity, temperature', 'Jesi Pebralia', 240, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS204-Jesi Pebralia.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS204-Jesi Pebralia.pdf', '2024-10-04 09:10:12', '2024-10-15 07:48:27'),
(205, 'engineering', 'oral presentation', 'Identification of the Distribution of Gadang House in Sijunjung Traditional Village, Nagari Padang Ranah', 'Ariyati*1), Nadya Bestnissa2), Al Busya Fuadi3), Soni Pratomo4)', '1,3) Prodi Arsitektur, Fakultas Teknik dan Perencanaan,Universitas Bung Hatta, Indonesia\n2,4) Prodi Arsitektur, Fakultas Teknik dan Ilmu Komputer, Universitas Adiwangsa Jambi, Indonesia', 'This paper critically examines how Rumah Gadang Architecture refers to the physical, material and cultural relationship between the tectonic aspects of the building and the place where the building is located. The research aims to identify the distribution of Rumah Gadang and provide a living understanding of the means, criteria, methods, and tools used to find out the distribution pattern of Rumah Gadang. This paper focuses on the Sijunjung Traditional village, Nagari Padang Ranah, based on the characteristics of its location. Nagari Padang Ranah is located in the hills with slope terrain, surrounding environment and climate. The analysis of the constructed work includes documentation and comparative investigation of the identification of damage to the foundation building elements and connections, as well as the dimensions and proportions of the building elements, their spacing, and the overall arrangement of the building. The research will also uncover the logical reasons and abstract meanings behind construction decisions to select materials, tools and methods to alter the soil concerning the building. Ultimately, this paper will contribute to a new and critical approach to understanding how the people of Nagari Padang Ranah have traditionally connected themselves to the place itself.', 'distribution, Gadang House, identify, Sijunjung', 'Nadya Bestnissa and Soni Pratomo', 242, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS205-Soni Pratomo.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS205-Soni Pratomo.pdf', '2024-10-07 06:37:27', '2024-10-15 07:49:32'),
(206, 'science', 'oral presentation', 'Identification of the Distribution of Gadang House in Sijunjung Traditional Village, Nagari Padang Ranah', 'Ariyati*1), Nadya Bestnissa2), Al Busya Fuadi3), Soni Pratomo4)', '1,3) Prodi Arsitektur, Fakultas Teknik dan Perencanaan,Universitas Bung Hatta, Indonesia\n2,4) Prodi Arsitektur, Fakultas Teknik dan Ilmu Komputer, Universitas Adiwangsa Jambi, Indonesia', 'This paper critically examines how Rumah Gadang Architecture refers to the physical, material and cultural relationship between the tectonic aspects of the building and the place where the building is located. The research aims to identify the distribution of Rumah Gadang and provide a living understanding of the means, criteria, methods, and tools used to find out the distribution pattern of Rumah Gadang. This paper focuses on the Sijunjung Traditional village, Nagari Padang Ranah, based on the characteristics of its location. Nagari Padang Ranah is located in the hills with slope terrain, surrounding environment and climate. The analysis of the constructed work includes documentation and comparative investigation of the identification of damage to the foundation building elements and connections, as well as the dimensions and proportions of the building elements, their spacing, and the overall arrangement of the building. The research will also uncover the logical reasons and abstract meanings behind construction decisions to select materials, tools and methods to alter the soil concerning the building. Ultimately, this paper will contribute to a new and critical approach to understanding how the people of Nagari Padang Ranah have traditionally connected themselves to the place itself.', 'distribution, Gadang House, identify, Sijunjung', 'Nadya Bestnissa and Soni Pratomo', 242, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', NULL, 'invoice/Invoice-ABS206-Soni Pratomo.pdf', '2024-10-07 06:40:10', '2024-10-07 07:07:57'),
