(237, 'ethnobiology', 'oral presentation', 'Ethnobotanical Exploration of Multiethnic Medicinal Plants in Jambi Province', 'Revis Asra, Anis Tatik Maryani, Upik Yelianti', 'Universitas Jambi', 'This research aims to document local knowledge about medicinal plants from several ethni in Jambi Province. Analyze the diversity of  of medicinal plants, processing processes, methods of use, analyze the value of the cultural index (Index Cultural Significance), the percentage of parts used (Plant Part Value) , knowing the cultivation and conservation of medicinal plants by multiethnic groups in Jambi. This research was conducted in Batang Sangir Village and Kersik Tuo Village, Kayu Aro District, Kerinci Regency for Javanese respondents, Limok Manaih Pulau Tengah Village, Keliling Danau District, Kerinci Regency for Kerinci Tribe respondents, Ulu Gedong Seberang Subdistrict, Jambi City for Malay respondents, Faculty of Science Laboratory and Technology, and Herbarium Anda, Andalas University, Padang. This  research is descriptive in nature using survey and in-depth interview methods. Respondents were determined using purposive sampling and snowball sampling. Based on the research results, it is known that there are 156 species from 61 plant families that are used as medicine. The part of the plant that is most widely used is the leaf part at 49.23% totaling (96), the highest ICS value is 72 in the species Zingiber officinale Roscoe, the lowest ICS value is 3 in the species Saracai indica L. and Salvia rosmarinus Spenn. The percentage value is based on the disease, the most common medicinal plant is diabetes (16.67%), and the percentage of the family most frequently used is the Zingiberaceae.', 'Medicinal Plants, Multiethnic, Jambi', 'Revis Asra', 275, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', NULL, 'invoice/Invoice-ABS237-Revis Asra.pdf', '2024-10-23 08:20:37', '2024-10-23 11:18:12'),
(238, 'stem_education', 'oral presentation', 'Implementation of Structural Equation Modeling (SEM) to analyze factors that influence the learning motivation of students at the Faculty of Science and Technology, Universitas Jambi ', 'Sarmada 1), Sherli Yurinanda *2), Syamsyida Rozi3),', '1)Mathematics Study Program, Faculty of Science and Technology, Universita Jambi, Indonesia\n2)Mathematics Study Program, Faculty of Science and Technology, Universita Jambi, Indonesia\n3)Mathematics Study Program, Faculty of Science and Technology, Universita Jambi, Indonesia', 'Learning motivation is an effort that drives learning activities to ensure the continuity of learning activities, so that the desired goals can be achieved. Thus, it is necessary to analyze the factors that influence students\' learning motivation. The number of samples in this study was 341 FST UNJA students from the 2021-2024 intake who were actively attending lectures. The research method used was a quantitative survey method where data collection was carried out using a questionnaire with a Likert scale. The data analysis method used was descriptive analysis and Structural Equation Modeling (SEM) analysis assisted by the AMOS 2.2 program. In this study, there were three exogenous variables used, namely learning methods, learning facilities and learning environment. While the endogenous variable used was learning motivation. The results of the study showed that the learning method variable had the greatest contribution, then the second variable that contributed to increasing learning motivation was the learning environment and finally the learning facilities had the smallest effect on learning motivation. So, all latent variables of learning methods, learning facilities and learning environment have a positive effect on learning motivation', 'Learning motivation, Structural Equation Modeling, Students', 'Sherli Yurinanda', 276, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS238-Sherli Yurinanda.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS238-Sherli Yurinanda.pdf', '2024-10-23 08:45:34', '2024-10-26 01:03:15'),
(239, 'digital_transformation_education', 'oral presentation', 'EDUKASI DINI SAMPAH ORGANIK DAN ANORGANIK  PADA ANAK PAUD TK AL-AQSHA KEC. TELANAIPURA KOTA JAMBI', 'Fetty Febriasti Bahar, Ira Galih Prabasari,  Winny Laura Christina Hutagalung,  Dyah Kumalasari,  Zuli Rodhiyah', 'Universitas Jambi', 'Anak dengan usia 1 – 3 tahun merupakan masa dimana edukasi dan disiplin perlu ditanamkan dengan cara yang menarik. Memberikan edukasi terkait sampah organik dan anorganik pada anak anak tersebut akan memberi hal positif berupa kesadaran lingkungan yang bermanfaat tidak saja bagi diri sendiri namun juga bagi lingkungan sekitar. Dengan melakukan pemilahan sampah berarti anak anak tersebut telah melakukan pengelolaan sampah awal yang akan memberi dampak yang baik bagi pengelolaan sampah selanjutnya. Tujuan dari pengabdian ini adalah untuk meningkatkan kesadaran akan kebersihan lingkungan dengan jalan memberikan edukasi dini tentang sampah organik dan anorganik pada anak PAUD TK Al-Aqsha Kecamatan Telanaipura Kota Jambi. Luaran yang ditargetkan dari pengabdian ini adalah publikasi pada jurnal nasional, pada media massa (cetak atau online), serta video kegiatan yang akan diunggah di channel youtube LPPM.', 'sampah; usia dini; edukasi ', 'Winny Laura Christina Hutagalung', 278, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS239-Winny Laura Christina Hutagalung.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS239-Winny Laura Christina Hutagalung.pdf', '2024-10-23 23:08:42', '2024-10-24 10:13:02'),
(240, 'sustainable_engineering', 'oral presentation', 'Perancangan Detail Engineering Design Rencana Pembangunan Tempat Pengolahan Sampah Terpadu  Universitas Jambi', 'Revis Asra, Hariestya Viareco, Oki Alfernando, Winny Laura, Dila Oktarise, Ade Nurdin, Fetty Febriasti, Dyah Kumalasari', 'Universitas Jambi', 'Sampah merupakan bahan yang terbuang atau dibuang dari suatu sumber hasil dari aktivitas manusia maupun proses-proses alami yang tidak mempunyai nilai ekonomi, bahkan dapat bernilai negatif akibat pengelolaannya baik itu dalam hal pembuangannya maupun pembersihannya dimana membutuhkan biaya yang lumayan besar. Universitas Jambi yang berkembang cukup pesat, terutama dalam hal fisik dan jumlah mahasiswa berimbas pada peningkatan volume timbulan sampah yang dihasilkan dimana nantinya dapat menimbulkan masalah jika tidak dikelola dengan baik. Oleh karena itu perlu adanya pembangunan Tempat Pengolahan Sampah Terpadu (TPST) di Universitas Jambi yang bisa menjadi salah satu Solusi dalam mengatasi permasalahan sampah yang muncul. Dalam Pembangunan TPST dibutuhkan dokumen awal yang disebut Detail Engineering Design (DED) sebagai acuan dalam Pembangunan TPST tersebut dan dokumen resmi yang wajib dimiliki untuk membangun suatu konstruksi bangunan. Melalui penelitian ini diharapakan nanti diperoleh dokumen Detail Engineering Design (DED) yang lengkap dimana terdiri dari gambar detail dan gambar rencana, rencana kerja dan syarat-syarat (RKS) dan rencana anggaran biaya (RAB). ', 'TPST; DED; gambar; RKS; RAB ', 'Winny Laura Christina Hutagalung', 278, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS240-Winny Laura Christina Hutagalung.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS240-Winny Laura Christina Hutagalung.pdf', '2024-10-23 23:24:55', '2024-10-25 02:52:15'),
(241, 'stem_education', 'oral presentation', 'Peningkatan Indeks Kepuasan Masyarakat: Strategi Inovatif untuk Meningkatkan Kualitas dan Layanan Pendidikan di Fakultas Sains dan Teknologi Universitas Jambi', 'Bambang Hariyadi, Ira Galih, Winny Laura, Ade Adriadi, Hisni Rahmi, Andre Rabiula', 'Universitas Jambi', 'Melalui indeks kepuasan Masyarakat, Fakultas Sains dan Teknologi (FST) akan mampu mengukur peranannya di dalam Masyarakat. Pengukuran indeks kepuasan Masyarakat dilakukan melalui penyebaran kuesioner indeks kepuasan Masyarakat kepada masyarakat yang memiliki dampak langsung kepada Fakultas Sains dan Teknologi seperti dosen, tenaga kependidikan, mahasiswa, alumni, dan mitra/pengguna lulusan. Tujuan dari penelitian ini adalah untuk mengetahui tingkat keberhasilan kinerja layanan di FST sebagai bahan untuk upaya peningkatan di tahun yang akan datang. Dengan menggunakan skala likert 1 – 4, dimana skala 4 untuk skala paling baik dan skala 1 untuk skala paling buruk, maka indeks kepuasan diharapkan berada pada skala sangat baik sampai baik dengan indeks 4 – 3. Indeks kepuasan kepada Masyarakat juga dapat berperan untuk pengembangan bagi layanan Fakultas Sains dan Teknologi. Adanya indeks skala 2 dan 1 pada penilaian kuesioner menjadi cermin bagi Fakultas Sains dan Teknologi untuk melakukan perbaikan. Luaran yang ditargetkan dari penelitian ini adalah terbitnya kuesioner indeks kepuasan masyarakat terhadap layanan Fakultas Sains dan Teknologi.', 'kepuasan masyarakat; layanan pendidikan, kuesioner', 'Winny Laura Christina Hutagalung', 278, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS241-Winny Laura Christina Hutagalung.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS241-Winny Laura Christina Hutagalung.pdf', '2024-10-23 23:33:00', '2024-10-24 10:12:31'),
(242, 'big_data_analytics', 'oral presentation', 'Early Bankruptcy Detection Analysis of Manufacturing Companies Using Machine Learning Algorithms', 'Tri Suratno*1), Zainil Abidin 2), Mutia Fadhila Putri 3)', 'Fakultas Sains & Teknologi \nUniversitas Jambi', 'Bankruptcy prediction is a critical aspect for stakeholders in assessing the financial health of companies, particularly in the manufacturing sector, which plays a vital role in Indonesia\'s economy. This study aims to develop an early bankruptcy detection model using machine learning algorithms to assist in predicting the risk of bankruptcy in manufacturing companies. Financial data from 164 manufacturing companies listed on the Indonesia Stock Exchange (IDX) were collected and analyzed, covering variables such as Working Capital, Total Assets, Retained Earnings, EBIT, Market Value of Equity, Total Liabilities, and Sales. The Altman Z-Score was used to categorize companies into bankrupt, high-risk, and healthy. Four machine learning algorithms—K-Nearest Neighbor (KNN), Naive Bayes Gaussian, Support Vector Classifier (SVC), and Decision Tree—were implemented to evaluate prediction accuracy. The results showed that SVC had the highest accuracy of 0.97, followed by Naive Bayes Gaussian (0.95), K-Nearest Neighbor (KNN) (0.94), and Decision Tree (0.79). These findings highlight the effectiveness of machine learning in early bankruptcy detection and can provide valuable insights for investors, regulators, and company management in making informed decisions.', 'bankruptcy, machine learning, financial health, Altman Z-Score, manufacturing companies', 'Tri Suratno, Zainil Abidin', 279, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS242-Tri Suratno.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS242-Tri Suratno.pdf', '2024-10-24 01:46:36', '2024-10-24 02:32:18'),
(243, 'advanced_material', 'oral presentation', 'Enhanced Mechanical Stabilization of Peat Soils Using Geopolymerization of Palm Oil Fuel Ash', 'Oki Alfernando, Dila Oktarise Dwina, Nurza Purwa Abiyoga', 'Universitas Jambi', 'Peat soils are characterized by high compressibility and low shear strength, which present significant construction and infrastructure development challenges. In Jambi, Indonesia, extensive peatland areas require innovative stabilization methods to enhance their mechanical properties for sustainable land use. This study investigates using palm oil fuel ash (POFA) as a base material for geopolymerization to stabilize peat soils. POFA, an industrial by-product, is abundant in the region and offers a sustainable alternative to traditional stabilizers. The research methodology involved the preparation of geopolymer-stabilized peat samples with 0%, 10%, 15%, and 20% POFA concentrations, followed by Unconfined Compressive Strength (UCS) tests to assess the improvement in soil strength. The results of the UCS tests indicate a positive trend in enhancing the peat’s mechanical properties, with increasing compressive strength values as the geopolymer content increases to 15%. The average UCS results for the consecutive amount of POFA addition are 15.10 kPa, 30.05 kPa, 37.90 kPa, and 9.71 kPa. In conclusion, using POFA-based geopolymer shows potential as an effective and sustainable solution for improving the strength characteristics of peat soils with a notable maximum amount of addition at 15%. This stabilization technique could provide a viable method for infrastructure development in peatland areas', 'geopolymer, unconfined compression strength, palm oil fuel ash, peat', 'Nurza Purwa Abiyoga', 272, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS243-Dila Oktarise Dwina.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS243-Dila Oktarise Dwina.pdf', '2024-10-24 02:37:18', '2024-10-25 02:53:56'),
(244, 'technopreneurship', 'oral presentation', 'Transformation of Economic Independence: Development of Tangkit Eco-Edu-Tourism Village Through Empowerment of Natural Resources Based on Family Medicinal Plants in RT 26, Tangkit Village, Sungai Gelam District, Muaro Jambi Regency', 'Ade Adriadi, Revis Asra, Oki Alfernando, Dila Oktarise Dwina, Dyah Kumalasari', 'Universitas Jambi', 'Brick-making is the main livelihood of the residents of RT 26 in Tangkit Village. However, the depletion of raw material sources has led to increased production costs, which in turn has reduced profits. This has impacted the community’s income. Therefore, it is necessary to develop alternative income sources to improve the community’s economy. One of the steps that can be taken is to develop Tangkit Village into an Eco-Edu-Tourism village based on medicinal family plants, utilizing the wealth of natural resources available in the village. Through this initiative, it is hoped that Tangkit Village can become a model village where the community can manage the village independently, both in terms of technology and economy, thereby supporting its economic sustainability. Additionally, it is expected that this initiative will generate new sources of income from the empowerment of the Eco-Edu-Tourism village, as well as foster a skilled, productive, and economically independent community.', 'Eco-Edu-Tourism, Community, Economic, sustainability', 'Ade Adriadi ', 272, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS244-Dila Oktarise Dwina.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS244-Dila Oktarise Dwina.pdf', '2024-10-24 02:53:11', '2024-10-25 02:53:19'),
(245, 'technopreneurship', 'oral presentation', 'Penerapan Sistem Audit Search Engine Optimization (SEO) Berbasis Perangkat Lunak Open Source', 'Daniel Arsa\nMutia Fadhila Putri\nMuhammad Razi A.\nKelvin Adinata', 'Universitas Jambi', 'Dalam tiga puluh tahun terakhir, perkembangan internet telah mengalami kemajuan pesat dari website sederhana menjadi platform yang ramah seluler. Dengan jumlah website yang semakin banyak, pengguna sering mengandalkan mesin pencari untuk mendapatkan informasi yang mereka cari. Untuk mendapatkan eksposur yang optimal, website perlu dioptimalkan untuk dapat muncul pada peringkat utama di mesin pencari seperti Google melalui praktik yang dikenal sebagai Search Engine Optimization (SEO). Penelitian ini berfokus pada pengembangan alat audit SEO yang tersedia secara gratis dan berbasis Open Source, yang bertujuan untuk membantu pemilik website meningkatkan peringkat mereka dalam hasil pencarian. Diharapkan dapat dilakukan analisis terhadap source code halaman web yang dimiliki, sekaligus menganalisis website pesaing untuk memberikan rekomendasi perbaikan yang diperlukan.  Inovasi ini diharapkan akan memberikan manfaat bagi pemilik website, digital marketer, dan pakar SEO tanpa memandang tingkat pengalaman mereka. Pengembangan alat SEO yang gratis ini diharapkan dapat mempermudah proses audit SEO, khususnya bagi organisasi nirlaba dan pemula yang mungkin tidak mampu membeli perangkat lunak SEO berbayar. Pada penelitian ini, sistem akan diuji pada website Universitas Jambi dengan keyword pencarian dan kompetitor yang sesuai.', 'SEO, Audit, Open Source, Search Engine, Website', 'Daniel Arsa', 281, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS245-Daniel Arsa.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS245-Daniel Arsa.pdf', '2024-10-24 03:03:53', '2024-10-24 04:36:27'),
(246, 'stem_education', 'oral presentation', 'Improving the Learning Outcomes of the Environmental Impact Analysis Course through Building Design Project Assignments in the Odd Semester of the Academic Year 2024/2025', '1. Shally Yanova\n2. Jalius', 'Jambi University', 'The project-based learning model is one of the learning systems that can be applied to the Environmental Impact Assessment course. This model is suitable for the concept of educational innovation in the field of environmental engineering, especially for students in achieving the learning outcomes of this course. The outcome of the Environmental Impact Assessment course is that students are able to plan construction projects and prepare environmental documents. Based on the results of the midterm exam of Jambi University Environmental Engineering students for the academic year 2024/2025, an average of 82.36 was obtained from 42 students. This result is higher than the midterm exam results for the 2023/2024 academic year with an average score of 80.84 from 35 students. In addition, based on the survey results, 95.24% of the students thought that the project assignments given in this course were able to improve the students\' understanding in this Environmental Impact Analysis course. Thus, it can be concluded that the implementation of building design project assignments and environmental documents is able to improve students\' understanding and fulfill the outcomes of the Environmental Impact Analysis course.', 'PjBL, EIA, Environmental Engineering, Jambi University, Academic Year 2024/2025', 'Shally Yanova', 268, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS246-Shally Yanova.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS246-Shally Yanova.pdf', '2024-10-24 03:12:57', '2024-10-25 04:01:56'),
(247, 'bio_technology', 'oral presentation', 'Network Pharmacology Analysis of Secondary Metabolites of Sungkai (Peronema Canescens Jack) as Anticancer', 'Ratih Dyah Puspitasari *1), Indra Lasmana Tarigan 2), Ahmad Sazali3) ', 'Universitas Jambi', 'Cervical cancer is a malignant cervix tumor caused by Human papillomavirus infection. Cancer drugs on the market, such as SAHA and Varinostat, are reported to have side effects, so there is still a need to develop new drugs. The drug discovery process requires quite expensive costs and a relatively long time. Aside from synthesis results, medicinal cancer therapy products also come from natural ingredients containing secondary metabolites. Sungkai plants contain secondary metabolites of alkaloids, terpenoids, steroids, flavonoids, phenolics, and saponins. The compounds are β-sitosterol, phytol, β-amyrin, Peronemin A1, A3, B1, B2, B3, C1, and D1, Peronemin A3 and C1. This research used the ADMET, QSAR, and network analysis study methods.  Extract Sungkai bioactives were predicted to act as an anticancer by targeting proteins associated with cervical cancer. STAT3 is one of the potential bioactive targets of Sungkai leaf extract because it correlates with the development of cervical cancer—regulation of gene expression, proliferation, inflammatory response, and regulation of apoptosis influenced by Sungkai leaf extract.', 'extract, sungkai, network analysis, anticancer', 'Ratih Dyah Puspitasari', 284, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS247-Ratih Dyah Puspitasari.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS247-Ratih Dyah Puspitasari.pdf', '2024-10-24 15:04:39', '2024-10-26 00:06:29'),
(248, 'bio_medic_technology', 'oral presentation', 'Formulation and Evaluation of Sunscreen Cream Containing Jernang Resin (Daemonorops draco (Willd.) Blume)', 'Revis Asra, Uce Lestari, Fitra Wahyuni, Tiara Nasela, Ajeng Aprina Azzahra', 'Jambi University', 'The type of dragon blood discovered in Jambi Province is jernang rambai (Daemonorops draco\n(Willd.) Blume), which can produce a higher quantity of resin with better quality compared to\nother types of jernang. Pharmacological research shows that jernang resin contains flavonoid,\npolyphenol, and triterpenoid compounds, which function to counteract free radicals, thus\nprotecting facial skin from sun exposure and skin damage such as sunburn and aging. Based\non this, jernang resin has the potential to serve as a sunscreen in the cosmetics industry. The\naim of this research is to formulate and evaluate a sunscreen cream made from the active\ningredient of jernang resin. The sunscreen cream was formulated using three different\nconcentrations of jernang resin (10%, 20%, and 30%) and underwent psychochemical\nparameter testing (colour, odour, homogeneity, spread ability and adhesion, pH, and emulsion\ntype). The results of this study indicate that all jernang rambai formulations have a pH range\nthat is suitable for the skin (5.8-6.25) and exhibit good adhesion, spread ability, homogeneity,\nconsistency, and have a m/a emulsion type. The conclusion of the research is that the sunscreen\ncream at concentrations of 10%, 20%, and 30% of jernang rambai meets the psychochemical\nparameter requirements.', 'Daemonorops draco (Willd.) Blume, psychochemical parameter, sunscreen formulation', 'Fitra Wahyuni', 282, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS248-Fitra.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS248-Fitra.pdf', '2024-10-24 17:54:04', '2024-10-25 04:02:27'),
(249, 'biodiversity', 'oral presentation', 'Community Service: Training on Creating Dry Herbarium as A Learning Media for Senior High School Students ', 'Revis Asra, Ade Adriadi, Dawam Suprayogi, Hasna Ul Maritsa, Fitra Wahyuni', 'Jambi University', 'The use of learning media can make the learning process more engaging, with teaching materials that are more tangible in their application, making it easier for students to understand and enhancing creativity as students engage in learning activities such as observing and demonstrating, rather than just listening to the teacher. One essential learning media in the biology teaching process is an herbarium. An herbarium is a collection of dried/preserved specimens, usually organized based on a classification system. Herbarium serves as an appropriate learning media because it can be taken anywhere, both in the classroom and in the laboratory. Therefore, to enhance the use of herbarium learning media in high schools, the biology study program at Jambi University conducted community service aimed at training students and teachers in creating simple herbariums as an environmentally based biology learning media. The methods used were tutorials and group mentoring for students and teachers. The results of this community service activity were very positive, as evidenced by the high enthusiasm of students and teachers in participating in the herbarium training. This community service increased knowledge and new skills about herbariums and their simple creation techniques. During this activity, five plant species were identified with their scientific names, and herbariums were created from the school environment, which can be used as teaching tools to support the achievement of learning objectives.', 'herbarium, learning media, senior high school, training', 'Fitra Wahyuni', 236, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS249-Revis Asra.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS249-Revis Asra.pdf', '2024-10-24 19:11:55', '2024-10-25 04:00:42'),
(250, 'big_data_analytics', 'oral presentation', 'DETERMINING THE CALENDAR OF PLANTING PERIOD BASED ON RAINFALL PREDICTION USING THE SARIMA METHOD', 'Mohammad Ilhami, Pradita Eko Prasetyo Utomo, Ulfa Khaira, Benedika Ferdian Hutabarat', 'Universitas Jambi', 'Rainfall data has been a benchmark that is often used in determining the start of rice planting using the Oldeman method. When rainfall in a particular month reaches 200 mm, it will be designated as the start of rice planting. With this method, the determination of the start of planting can change according to changes in climatic conditions. An early planting season approach using rainfall data will generally be suitable for areas with the main water source being rainwater. One of the climate elements most widely used in research is rainfall, which is closely related to determining the planting calendar. So, forecasting rainfall conditions will be very useful for the agricultural sector in determining the planting calendar. Therefore, considering the importance of rainwater for plants, especially rice, in this research it is proposed to apply rainfall predictions using the Seasonal ARIMA method which is a form of the ARIMA method that takes into account seasonal patterns.  The ARIMA method was chosen because it is able to accommodate extreme values, in this case rainfall which is usually seasonal, as well as the availability of rainfall data in monthly form', 'SARIMA, Forecasting, Oldeman, Rainfall, rice', 'Pradita Eko Prasetyo Utomo', 248, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS250-Pradita Eko Prasetyo Utomo.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS250-Pradita Eko Prasetyo Utomo.pdf', '2024-10-25 00:40:38', '2024-10-26 11:41:41'),
(251, 'digital_transformation_education', 'oral presentation', 'Evaluation of the Implementation BISMA Application through Black Box Testing approach', 'Pradita Eko Prasetyo Utomo, Jodion Siburian, Dawam Suprayogi', 'Universitas Jambi', 'This study evaluates the BISMA application, recently implemented at Universitas Jambi for managing research and community service, through black-box testing. Despite the system\'s initial launch, it is essential to assess how effectively BISMA improves user confidence and decision-making processes within academic settings. This research aims to measure user trust in BISMA, analyze its role in decision support for research and community service, and identify factors influencing user satisfaction. The study employs descriptive quantitative methods, gathering primary data through surveys and interviews with system users, including university administrators and faculty members. Key findings will inform further development of the BISMA application to enhance functionality, accuracy, and efficiency, ultimately leading to better support for decision-making and user satisfaction. The anticipated outcomes include actionable recommendations for system improvements, the creation of a real-time data dashboard, and increased user confidence in BISMA\'s capabilities.', 'BISMA, BlackBox, testing, user, satisfaction', 'Pradita Eko Prasetyo Utomo', 248, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS251-Pradita Eko Prasetyo Utomo.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS251-Pradita Eko Prasetyo Utomo.pdf', '2024-10-25 00:48:33', '2024-10-26 11:42:14'),
(252, 'digital_transformation_education', 'oral presentation', 'Pemanfaatan Teknologi Informasi Pada Praktek Dokter Bersama Patimura Untuk Meningkatkan Produktivitas Kerja', 'Tri Suratno, Reni Aryani, Zainil Abidin, Yolla Noverina, Mohamad Ilhami', 'Fakultas Sains &Teknologi Universitas Jambi', 'Klinik Praktek Dokter Bersama Patimura menghadapi beberapa kendala dalam operasionalnya, terutama terkait dengan penggunaan teknologi informasi. Aktivitas bisnis di klinik masih dilakukan secara manual dan konvensional. Berkas administrasi klinik, termasuk data pasien dan rekam medis, belum terintegrasi dalam sistem komputer, sehingga menimbulkan inefisiensi dalam pengarsipan dan pengelolaan data. Selain itu, keterampilan pegawai dalam bidang teknologi informasi dan komunikasi (TIK) masih terbatas, yang menghambat produktivitas kerja. Berdasarkan analisis situasi ini, solusi yang ditawarkan melalui program pengabdian kepada masyarakat adalah memberikan pendampingan dan pelatihan intensif kepada pegawai klinik untuk meningkatkan keterampilan mereka dalam penggunaan TIK. Pelatihan ini dilakukan dalam dua sesi utama: (1) sosialisasi mengenai peran penting TIK dalam kegiatan bisnis sehari-hari dan manfaat penggunaannya, dan (2) pendampingan dan pelatihan teknis menggunakan aplikasi Microsoft Word, Excel, serta pemanfaatan internet secara optimal. Hasil dari kegiatan ini diharapkan dapat meningkatkan keterampilan pegawai dalam menggunakan TIK, sehingga proses administrasi di klinik menjadi lebih efisien dan produktivitas kerja meningkat. Melalui kegiatan ini, diharapkan terjadi peningkatan keterampilan pegawai dalam mengoperasikan teknologi informasi sehingga produktivitas kerja di Klinik Praktek Dokter Bersama Patimura dapat meningkat secara signifikan', 'Keterampilan computer, Pemanfaatan teknologi, informasi, komunikasi', 'Tri Suratno, Reni Aryani, Zainil Abidin, Yolla Noverina', 279, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS252-Tri Suratno.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS252-Tri Suratno.pdf', '2024-10-25 01:30:34', '2024-10-25 04:01:25'),
(253, 'sustainable_engineering', 'oral presentation', 'MOUNTAIN CLIMBING SUPPORT SYSTEM FOR GUNUNG KERINCI: Technological Solutions Through Virtual Reality, Path Tracking, and Warning System ', 'Edi Saputra, Reni Aryani, Mutia Fadhila Putri, Jefri Marzal', 'Universitas Jambi', 'This research aims to improve the safety and monitoring of Mount Kerinci climbing through the development of a web-based integrated information system. As the highest volcano in Southeast Asia, Mount Kerinci attracts many climbers, but the absence of a system to monitor climbers\' positions and volcanic status in real-time increases the risk of accidents. As a solution, a web-based Integrated Information System was developed to support the management of Kerinci Seblat National Park in monitoring climbing activities. The development of this system uses the Scrum method, which allows flexible development through continuous iteration. The system has five main features: 1) Climber Monitoring Dashboard to track active climbers and their positions; 2) Mountain Monitoring Dashboard to provide mountain status and weather information; 3) Climber Tracking that visualizes the climbing path that has been traversed; 4) Climber Registration to manage climber data; and 5) Virtual Reality (VR) that provides a simulation of the climbing path. This research makes an important contribution in supporting technology-based adventure tourism management, as well as improving climbing safety on Mount Kerinci.', 'hiking safety, Kerinci Mount, ecotourism technology', 'Reni Aryani', 265, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS253-Reni Aryani.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS253-Reni Aryani.pdf', '2024-10-25 01:44:33', '2024-10-26 03:07:08'),
(254, 'digital_transformation_education', 'oral presentation', 'Digital Literacy Training for IT Ash-Shiddiqi Middle School Students to be Wise in Using Digital Technology', 'Reni Aryani, Muhammad Razi. A, Tri Suratno, Benedika Ferdian Hutabarat, Rizqa Raaiqa Bintana', 'Universitas Jambi', 'In the ever-evolving digital era, ensuring that young people have comprehensive digital literacy skills is essential. This activity focuses on a training program implemented at SMP IT Ash-Shiddiiqi to address students’ lack of understanding of digital literacy. Although students tend to be adept at using digital technology, they often lack adequate knowledge about how to safely and responsibly interact in the digital world. The program is designed in two phases: the first phase focuses on basic knowledge about the benefits and risks of digital technology, while the second phase provides practical training to strengthen digital security practices. This initiative aims to equip students with the necessary competencies to participate safely and responsibly on digital platforms. The outcome of this activity was a significant increase in digital awareness and security practices among participants, and supports the broader educational goal of producing digitally competent and responsible learners.', 'digital literacy, junior high school students, digital media literacy', 'Reni Aryani', 265, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS254-Reni Aryani.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS254-Reni Aryani.pdf', '2024-10-25 02:05:41', '2024-10-26 03:07:37'),
(255, 'bio_medic_technology', 'oral presentation', 'Modeling Morbidity Table for Chronic Diseases Based on Prevalence Rates', 'Khairul Alim, Gusmi Kholijah, Meinarisa', 'Universitas Jambi', 'Morbidity tables are essential tools in healthcare and actuarial science that provide an overview of disease prevalence within a population at a given time. These tables aid in comparing disease rates between populations, assessing the success of health programs, and predicting future healthcare needs. In health insurance, morbidity tables play a key role in determining fair premium rates for both the public and insurance providers. However, constructing such tables in Indonesia poses challenges, particularly due to its vast geographical landscape. To address this, the study uses disease prevalence rates for modeling, as they are easier to obtain in regions with smaller populations. This research focuses on developing morbidity table for chronic diseases, modeled using a multi-state approach that includes the statuses of healthy, sick, and deceased. The transition from healthy to sick is modeled using a piecewise constant function, while mortality risk is modeled using the Gompertz-Makeham model.', 'morbidity table, prevalence, chronic diseases, Gompertz-Makeham', 'Khairul Alim', 232, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS255-Khairul Alim.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS255-Khairul Alim.pdf', '2024-10-25 03:17:46', '2024-10-26 02:15:17'),
(256, 'bio_technology', 'oral presentation', 'Utilization of Organic Waste at Three Senior High School of Jambi as an Eco-Friendly Multipurpose Liquid', 'Mahya Ihsan, Ade Adriadi, Tia Wulandari, Ahmad Sazali, Fitra Wahyuni', 'Universitas Jambi', 'Household waste can be utilized for useful products such as eco-enzyme and liquid organic fertilizer. Due to this, the community services team from university of jambi organized an training activity on making liquid organic fertilizer and eco-enzyme for students at SMAN 3 Muara Jambi. the results obtained are products innovative that can be utilized as products for entreprenuership  for students.', 'Liquid organic fertilizer, eco-enzyme, community services', 'Ade Adriadi', 234, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS256-Ade Adriadi.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS256-Ade Adriadi.pdf', '2024-10-25 09:15:08', '2024-10-25 09:32:32'),
(257, 'sustainable_engineering', 'oral presentation', 'Design and implementation of integrity zone in Faculty of Science and Technology, Jambi University', 'Dr. Madyawati Latief, S.P.,\r M.Si.\r\nAlrizaf, S.Pd., M.Si.\r\nFernando Mersa Putra,\r S.T., M.Sc.\r\nSherli Yurinanda, S.Pd.,\r M,Si.', 'Universitas Jambi ', 'This research aims to design and implement a Integrity Zone (ZI) model at the Faculty of Science and Technology, Jambi University (FST UNJA) using a mixed-method, combining qualitative and quantitative methods, for a comprehensive understanding. The study begins with literature review and policy analysis to fully understand the concepts of ZI, bureaucratic reform, and good governance in higher education level (university), alongside reviewing related national and institutional policies that are related to ZI. \nThis research also involves benchmarking to BPMP Jambi, to identify best practices that they have developed, problems and also challenges that they faced in their journey to achieve WBK zone award.\nA conceptual ZI model is then developed and validated through expert involvement. The research also includes designing instruments like questionnaires, interview guidelines, and observation rubrics, tested for validity and reliability before it Will be used as a baseline for data collection. \nSurveys and internal audits will be done to measure academic community understanding and perceptions of ZI while assessing existing systems and procedures in FST UNJA. The ZI implementation model starts with a pilot project in selected units at FST UNJA, accompanied by regular monitoring and evaluation. Collected data are analyzed using descriptive and inferential methods for quantitative data, and thematic analysis for qualitative data. Pilot project evaluation results then Will be used to refine the ZI model, formulate recommendations policy and also implementation strategy for FST UNJA. Finally, research findings are disseminated through reports, scientific articles, and presentations to stakeholders and the academic community.', 'Integrity zone, Implementation, Design', 'Fernando Mersa Putra', 285, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', NULL, 'invoice/Invoice-ABS257-Fernando Mersa Putra.pdf', '2024-10-25 10:56:05', '2024-10-25 23:40:25'),
(258, 'socio_engineering', 'oral presentation', 'Design and Implementation of Integrity Zone in Faculty of Science and Technology, Jambi University', 'Dr. Madyawati Latief, S.P.,\nM.Si.\nAlrizaf, S.Pd., M.Si.\nFernando Mersa Putra,\nS.T., M.Sc.\nSherli Yurinanda, S.Pd.,\nM,Si.\nFitra Wahyuni, S.Si., M.Si.\nDaniel Arsa, S.Kom., M.S.I.\nMuhammad El Hakim, S.T., M.T.\nFebri Berthalita Pujaningsih, S.Si., M.Si', 'Universitas Jambi', 'This research aims to design and implement a Integrity Zone (ZI) model at the Faculty of Science and Technology, Jambi University (FST UNJA) using a mixed-method, combining qualitative and quantitative methods, for a comprehensive understanding. The study begins with literature review and policy analysis to fully understand the concepts of ZI, bureaucratic reform, and good governance in higher education level (university), alongside reviewing related national and institutional policies that are related to ZI. \nThis research also involves benchmarking to BPMP Jambi, to identify best practices that they have developed, problems and also challenges that they faced in their journey to achieve WBK zone award.\nA conceptual ZI model is then developed and validated through expert involvement. The research also includes designing instruments like questionnaires, interview guidelines, and observation rubrics, tested for validity and reliability before it Will be used as a baseline for data collection. \nSurveys and internal audits will be done to measure academic community understanding and perceptions of ZI while assessing existing systems and procedures in FST UNJA. The ZI implementation model starts with a pilot project in selected units at FST UNJA, accompanied by regular monitoring and evaluation. Collected data are analyzed using descriptive and inferential methods for quantitative data, and thematic analysis for qualitative data. Pilot project evaluation results then Will be used to refine the ZI model, formulate recommendations policy and also implementation strategy for FST UNJA. Finally, research findings are disseminated through reports, scientific articles, and presentations to stakeholders and the academic community.', 'Integrity zone, Design, Implementation', 'Fernando Mersa Putra', 285, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS258-Fernando Mersa Putra.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS258-Fernando Mersa Putra.pdf', '2024-10-25 11:17:25', '2024-10-26 10:48:42'),
(259, 'stem_education', 'oral presentation', 'Laboratory Security Transformation: Utilizing IoT Technology for Toxic Gas Detection in the Faculty of Science and Technology Laboratories', 'Zainil Abidin\nAndre Rabiula\nMuhammad Razi A.\nDhian Eka Wijaya', 'Fakultas Sains dan Teknologi, Universitas Jambi, Jambi', 'This study aims to enhance laboratory security through an innovative system that leverages Internet of Things (IoT) technology for toxic gas detection within the Faculty of Science and Technology laboratories. Academic laboratories, particularly in higher education institutions, are often at high risk for hazardous gas leaks, which pose significant dangers to users and the surrounding environment. By integrating IoT, this research seeks to create a toxic gas detection system that connects directly to the network, enabling real-time monitoring and rapid alerts via an Android application. The continuous data collection from this system allows for analyzing laboratory safety trends, identifying leakage patterns, and providing recommendations for preventive measures. The research methodology encompasses the design and development of both hardware and software components, trial runs in a simulated laboratory environment, and subsequent implementation and evaluation within the Faculty of Science and Technology laboratories. The current phase has successfully completed device construction and installation. The findings of this research are expected to significantly improve laboratory safety, reduce accident risks, and optimize toxic gas risk management within academic settings. Moreover, this research can serve as a foundation for developing similar technologies in industrial and other environmental sectors.', 'laboratory security, IoT, toxic gas detection, real-time monitoring, risk management', 'Zainil Abidin', 286, 'accepted', 'administrator@unja.ac.id', 'letter-of-acceptance/LOA-ABS259-Zainil Abidin.pdf', 'invoice/Invoice-ABS259-Zainil Abidin.pdf', '2024-10-25 13:02:42', '2024-10-26 01:00:26');
